08/04/2003
MOSTAR, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Ambassador to BiH Clifford Bond launched a campaign Monday (7 April) about US economic programmes to encourage trade and entrepreneurship in BiH.
The three-day campaign is being introduced in Mostar, Sarajevo, Tuzla and Banja Luka.
In other news, Republika Srpska Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic met representatives of the German association for technical co-operation, GTZ, to discuss possibilities for bilateral co-operation.
Another session will be held later this month.
Meanwhile, BiH Foreign Minister Mladen Ivanic visited Ljubljana on Monday, meeting with his Slovene counterpart Dimitri Rupel and others.
He signed a bilateral agreement on customs co-operation and discussed the frozen foreign currency deposits held by BiH citizens in one of the former Yugoslav banks - Ljubljanska Banka.
(OHR Sources - 08/04/03;
PBS BiH, RS government web site, Onasa, Radio Slovenia, BBC - 07/04/03)
